Comparing classical C.I.s with C.I.s found by VST

Aditya Ghosh

08/05/2021

  • Poisson classical C.I. v/s VST C.I.
  • Binomial classical C.I. v/s VST C.I.
  • BVN sample correlation classical v/s VST

Poisson classical C.I. v/s VST C.I.

z = qnorm(0.025, lower.tail = F)

poi.exmpl<-function(theta, n, flag = 0 ){
    x = rpois(n, theta)
    xbar = mean(x)
    swd = z*sqrt(xbar)/sqrt(n) 
    lwr = xbar - swd; uppr = xbar + swd
    if((theta < lwr) || (theta > uppr)) cl = 0
    else cl = 1
    if(flag != 0) cat("\nclassic 95% c.i. [", lwr, ",", uppr, "], width = ", uppr - lwr, "\n\n")
    swd = z/(2*sqrt(n))
    lwr = max(sqrt(xbar) - swd, 0)^2 ; uppr = (sqrt(xbar) + swd)^2
    if((theta < lwr) || (theta > uppr)) vs = 0
    else vs = 1
    if(flag != 0) cat("vst 95% c.i. [", lwr, ",", uppr, "], width = ", uppr - lwr, "\n\n")
    return(list(clssc = cl, vst = vs))
}

theta = 3; n = 30
poi.exmpl(theta, n, flag = 1)

Binomial classical C.I. v/s VST C.I.

z = qnorm(0.025, lower.tail = F)

bin.exmpl<-function(theta, n, flag = 0){
    x = rbinom(n, 1, theta)
    xbar = mean(x)
    swd = z*sqrt(xbar*(1 - xbar))/sqrt(n) 
    lwr = xbar - swd; uppr = xbar + swd
    if((theta < lwr) || (theta > uppr)) cl = 0
    else cl = 1
    if(flag != 0) cat("\nclassic 95% c.i. [", lwr, ",", uppr, "], width = ", uppr - lwr, "\n\n")
    swd = z/(2*sqrt(n))
    lwr = sin(max(asin(xbar) - swd, 0)) ; uppr = sin(min(asin(xbar) + swd, pi/2))
    if((theta < lwr) || (theta > uppr)) vs = 0
    else vs = 1
    if(flag != 0) cat("vst 95% c.i. [", lwr, ",", uppr, "], width = ", uppr - lwr, "\n\n")
    return(list(clssc = cl, vst = vs))
}

theta = 0.5; n = 30
bin.exmpl(theta, n, flag = 1)

BVN sample correlation classical v/s VST

library(MASS)
smplcorr<-function(rho, n){
    x = rnorm(n)
    y = rho * x + sqrt(1 - rho^2) * rnorm(n)
    return(cor(x, y))
}
# mygen generates B realisations of that statistic, for a fixed n.
mygen<-function(n, B){  
    z = c()
    for(b in 1:B) z = c(z, smplcorr(rho, n))
    r.cls = sqrt(n)*(z - rho)/(1-rho^2)
    r.vst = sqrt(n)*(atanh(z) - atanh(rho))
    return(list(rc = r.cls, rv = r.vst))
}

rho = 0.5; n = 20; B = 100
mygen(n, B)

Next, we compare the sample distn with theoretical distn.

set.seed(2027)
rho = 0.5
nlist = seq(30, 150, by = 30)
B = 5000 # number of realizations of the statistic that will be generated
cols = rainbow(l <- length(nlist))
sampled.c = sampled.v = NULL
for(i in 1:l){
    new <- mygen(nlist[i], B)
    sampled.c = cbind(sampled.c, new$rc)
    sampled.v = cbind(sampled.v, new$rv)
}

par(family = "System Font", mfrow = c(1, 2))
curve(dnorm(x), xlim = c(-3, 3), ylab = "estimated density", lwd = 2)
title(main = "Classical", line = 1, cex = 0.9)
for(j in 1:l)   lines(density(sampled.c[,j], kernel = "gaussian"), col = cols[j])
legend("topright", legend = nlist, col = cols, lwd = 2, title = "sample size(n)", cex = 0.9)
curve(dnorm(x), xlim = c(-3, 3), ylab = "estimated density", lwd = 2)
title(main = "VST", line = 1, cex = 0.9)
for(j in 1:l)   lines(density(sampled.v[,j], kernel = "gaussian"), col = cols[j])
legend("topright", legend = nlist, col = cols, lwd = 2, title = "sample size(n)", cex = 0.9)

par(family = "System Font", mfrow = c(1, 2), mar = c(3, 4.5, 2, 1))
curve(pnorm(x), xlim = c(-3, 3), lwd = 2, ylab = "CDF/ECDF")
title(main = "Classical", line = 1, cex = 0.9)
for(j in 1:l) lines(ecdf(sampled.c[,j]), col = cols[j], verticals=TRUE, do.points=FALSE, lty = 2)
legend("right", legend = nlist, col = cols, lwd = 2, title = "sample size(n)", cex = 0.9)
curve(pnorm(x), xlim = c(-3, 3), lwd = 2, ylab = "CDF/ECDF")
title(main = "VST", line = 1, cex = 0.9)
for(j in 1:l) lines(ecdf(sampled.v[,j]), col = cols[j], verticals=TRUE, do.points=FALSE, lty = 2)
legend("right", legend = nlist, col = cols, lwd = 2, title = "sample size(n)", cex = 0.9)

pvals.ks1 <- apply(sampled.c, 2, function(x) ks.test(x, "pnorm")$p.value)
pvals.chi1 <- apply(sampled.c, 2, function(x) chisq.test(table(cut(x, breaks = qnorm(seq(0, 1, by = 0.1)))), p = rep(0.1, 10))$p.value)
pvals.ks2 <- apply(sampled.v, 2, function(x) ks.test(x, "pnorm")$p.value)
pvals.chi2 <- apply(sampled.v, 2, function(x) chisq.test(table(cut(x, breaks = qnorm(seq(0, 1, by = 0.1)))), p = rep(0.1, 10))$p.value)

pvals.ks = cbind(pvals.ks1, pvals.ks2)
pvals.chi = cbind(pvals.chi1, pvals.chi2)
colnames(pvals.ks) = c("classical", "vst")

Next we try varying \(rho\).

mygen2<-function(n, B, rho){    
    z = c()
    for(b in 1:B) z = c(z, smplcorr(rho, n))
    r.cls = sqrt(n)*(z - rho)/(1-rho^2)
    r.vst = sqrt(n)*(atanh(z) - atanh(rho))
    return(list(rc = r.cls, rv = r.vst))
}

# for n = 30 and different values of rho
